Title: Make KCrash and Linux sandbox integration optional on iOS

## Problem

Kirigami Addons currently includes iOS in several broad non-Android or
non-Windows platform branches. This causes an iOS build to require and use
desktop-specific facilities:

- KF6Crash is required, linked, and initialized by the application helpers.
- `KSandbox` is included by the About component even though its packaging
  detection is Linux-specific.

KCrash depends on process and signal handling assumptions that are not
available or appropriate in the iOS application model. Requiring it prevents
Kirigami Addons from being cross-compiled for iOS. The sandbox packaging code
is relevant only to Linux package formats and should not be exposed to an iOS
translation unit.

## Proposed change

Do not require, link, include, or initialize KCrash when targeting iOS. Also
exclude the KSandbox include and Linux package-format detection from iOS
builds.

KIconThemes, Qt Widgets, and the rest of the Kirigami application defaults
remain enabled where they are otherwise supported.

## Impact

Kirigami Addons applications on iOS do not install KCrash handlers and do not
report Linux packaging information. Existing behavior on desktop platforms and
Android remains unchanged.

